        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "@barrettruth, ‾is `//?C:/` a valid path?‾ I just noticed you also linked this [article](https://learn.microsoft.com/en-us/dotnet/standard/io/file-path-formats) in the #39841, but I'll list the cases here as well for discussion :D¥nSo far, there are 3 file path formats on Windows:¥n* Traditional DOS paths (leading drive `:¥¥`...): `C:¥¥foo¥¥bar`, `¥¥foo¥¥bar`, `foo¥¥bar`, `.¥¥foo`, `..¥¥foo`, `C:foo¥¥bar`¥n* UNC paths (leading `¥¥¥¥`): `¥¥¥¥localhost¥¥C$¥¥foo¥¥bar`, `¥¥¥¥remote¥¥share¥¥foo¥¥bar`¥n* DOS device paths (leading `¥¥¥¥.¥¥`, `¥¥¥¥?¥¥`): `¥¥¥¥.¥¥C:¥¥foo¥¥bar`, `¥¥¥¥?¥¥C:¥¥foo¥¥bar`, `¥¥¥¥.¥¥Volume{xxxx}¥¥foo¥¥bar`,¥n  `¥¥¥¥?¥¥Volume{xxxx}¥¥foo¥¥bar`, `¥¥¥¥.¥¥UNC¥¥Server¥¥Share¥¥foo¥¥bar`¥n¥nPersonally, I think we can gradually support all the cases above, and it would be ideal if they could live in a single piece of logic, though I窶冦 not sure yet how well C and Lua can share it.¥nBTW, I was planning to look into this after slash normalization, since our support for `¥¥¥¥?¥¥` isn't great so far. But splitting it out now also seems fine窶杯his part might be portable back to Vim, while slash normalization may be harder :)¥n",
