        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Another unc scenario to consider that I don't see explicitly listed in this issue or other similar issues, is handling network shares mounted to a drive letter. I would like that if I `:cd P:/somepath` where P is a mounted share path, it should not normalize to the full unc path but rather stay `P:/somepath`¥n¥nMotivating example: Last year (Nov/Dec), I was trying to see if I could move my workspace to a share folder but I kept having issues with LSPs (unsure if client or server bugs and maybe recent path normalization work has fixed this). (Aside: the main issue was lsp updates to diagnostics, sematic tokens, etc wouldn't get updated so there is a high chance recent changes could have fixed this) I then tried mounting the share folder to a drive letter and making it the cwd, but it would always get normalized to the full unc path. I eventually gave up on using the share folder as a result.",
