        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I haven't noticed directory specifically, but I've seen that `expand('%:p')` can return a UNC path.¥n```pwsh¥n# add a `share` folder¥nmkdir 0¥nnvim 0¥¥demo.md¥n:echo expand('%:p')¥n```¥n¥nWhen opening the file, we rely on `libuv` and `GetFinalPathNameByHandleW` to resolve the real path, but in this case, it only returns the UNC path. As path normalization work moves forward, we may be able to find a way to address this. :) ¥n¥n<img height=¥"80¥" alt=¥"Image¥" src=¥"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f1ce4924-5f44-4d2e-8351-bbcb5d39ea23¥" />",
